The Soweto Uprisings took place 46 years ago. The movie about that watershed moment is celebrating its 30th anniversary and it's remained popular. eNCA speaks to Movie-mogul Anant Singh, who produced the film. Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - The Soweto Uprisings took place 46 years ago. The movie about that watershed moment is celebrating its 30th anniversary and it's remained popular. READ: On banning in contemporary South Africa: slouching towards Not-Bethlehem Sarafina starred Whoopi Goldberg, John Kani, Leleti Khumalo, and Miriam Makeba. Film producer Anant Singh reflects on the legacy of the movie in the video above. 